abstract: Times photographers spread out across the country to document the final days of the campaign, from Florida to California, Arizona to Pennsylvania.
snippet: Times photographers spread out across the country to document the final days of the campaign, from Florida to California, Arizona to Pennsylvania.
lead_paragraph: Months of rallying, handshaking and sign-waving reached an apex as the 2018 midterm elections came to an end on Tuesday. Democrats took control of the House of Representatives, but Republicans appeared likely to expand their majority in the Senate. Democrats also won in several governors races, but Republicans held on in swing states like Florida and Ohio. Several races around the country remained too close to call.

abstract: Mr. Deripaska has spent millions building influence in Washington and London. Now he awaits a key decision from the Trump administration.
snippet: Mr. Deripaska has spent millions building influence in Washington and London. Now he awaits a key decision from the Trump administration.
lead_paragraph: This spring, a British lord with deep ties to the governing Conservative Party and a reputation as a do-gooder environmentalist arrived in Washington on an unlikely mission: to save the business empire of Oleg Deripaska, one of Russias most infamous oligarchs.
